  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It has to do with my pain all these years, especially when it came before a holiday.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My chil-- our children never knew what it meant to have--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Grandparents.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For that matter, relatives.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Relatives.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Close relatives.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as the-- it seems that when the-- the German-- the Russian front was getting close-- the Russians were getting closer and closer to Poland-- I mean, into Poland, to-- to Lodz, the ghetto, they decided to liquidate the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Just the other day I read-- I happened to have here the prosecuting papers against-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I mentioned the man's name before.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The one that-- that sent us right and left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Biebow, right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because the same Biebow, what I didn't-- forgot to tell you before, is when we were sent away-- those that were able to work got sent to the Lodz ghetto-- he stood on a pile of stones and talking to those healthier ones.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Being probably afraid we shouldn't rise up or do anything or kill anyone, he gave a speech in German that we're going now to a place where we'll work and we will have Apfel und Apfelsine, which means apples and oranges.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is how good we're going to have it there, and if we work, we will be rewarded very well for our-- for our-- four our work.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This same man-- I just, you know, read this-- I happened to have this-- very few people have this prosecuting-- the documents-- that he was sentenced to death and he was executed in-- in Poland.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The plans, how he was-- wanted to extend the Lodz ghetto to use the Jewish people to the point as much as physically as they can give for the German effort and then destroy them.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
